# Pick a skill to update

You are driving a `gather-update` human task. The
`find-skill` task has already discovered all installed skills.

Read `{{ upstream['find-skill'].task_path }}` to see the
list. Show the user the available skills (name + namespace),
ask which one to update, and ask what changes they want to
make.

## Output

Write a YAML file matching `schemas/gather_update.yaml`:

```yaml
name: editor
namespace: home
path: /home/x/.kiro/skills/home/editor
type: interface
description: |
  Free-form description of the changes the user wants.
```

The `path` and `type` fields MUST come from `find-skill.skills[]`
for the chosen skill — do not synthesize them.
